metadata.name: Zaratan #307
metadata.description:
The Generative Token chooses between three primitives (cubes, spheres, triangle stripes) and places it along a parametric curve with parameters varying with noise() function as source of smooth motion.

New shapes are added layer after layer with new forms and colors.

At any time the user can pause the generation by pressing 'p', resume it with 'r' and save a 1600x1600 png with 's'.

Sources of variations are:
- primitives choice (3)
- orientation (0, 90, 180, 270 degrees)
- initial conditions
- shapes evolution
- colors evolution (only 10% will be bi-chromatic)


Press:
- 'p' to pause
- 'r' to resume
- 's' to save a 1600x1600 png image

metadata.name: Tangled #284
metadata.description:
"Tangled" is a generative art project that explores the emergent behaviour of simple shapes moving according to a random flow field. While the final result is always constrained to the shape of a circle, the variation within is endless.

Instructions:
Press "p" to pause the animation.
In live mode, press 1 through 5 to save a PNG version of the final result. The following resolutions are available:
1: 400 x 400 (ideal for Twitter PFP)
2: 1000 x 1000
3: 2000 x 2000
4: 4000 x 4000
5: 5000 x 5000
Please be patient, generating the PNG may take some time!

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: Juxtapose #30
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Juxtapose' is a series of bold, striking images each with a 'vintage' color palette (principal color is either green, red, blue, grey or yellow).

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1440x2000px PNG.

metadata.name: Fireworks #10
metadata.description:
Every token can output in 12 different aspect ratios:
1x1, 3x1, 3x2, 2x3, 4x3, 3x4, 5x4, 4x5, 16x9, 9x16, 16x10, 10x16

With 3 framing options:
1. No frame
2. Rectangle frame
3. Arched window

And downloadable in 4 different resolutions:
1. 1000px
2. 2000px
3. 4000px
4. 8000px

Click on the image in live view to unlock all these possibilities.

Made with p5.js.
Primary split 5% with The Processing Foundation.

metadata.name: Elementary Cellular Emoji Automata #766
metadata.description:
Features the full set of 1761 emojis, including skin tone and gender modifiers and all flags.
Arranged using the full 256 ruleset of one-dimensional cellular automata

If “random seed” is true then the seed of the generation is randomized using Math.random() meaning that the pattern will change on regeneration.
The ruleset, emoji, colors and all other properties will remain the same.

Auto-adjusts to screen size

Compatible with as many browsers and systems as possible

metadata.name: Light, shape and color #26
metadata.description:
Is the color real?... Is the color light? Is the color movement? The essence of color lies in "the awareness of the instability of reality". Color is a circumstance in time and space and not a certainty. Color manifests itself in space and can survive outside the support and form. It is a living essence.

This new generative work is based on the study and reflections of master Carlos Cruz-Diez on color and movement. In my student days, I lived among the master's chrome-saturated works. Caracas is a museum of the works of Cruz-Diez. This somehow had or has an influence on my perception of color.

[...] Color is "an ephemeral situation, an autonomous reality in continuous mutation" and, like events, it unfolds "in real space and time, without past or future, in a perpetual present" [...]

Carlos Cruz-Diez (1923-2019)

by Daniel Oropeza
Tw: @ferdoropeza

metadata.name: TENDER Pass #856
metadata.description:
Tender is a curatorial platform and community that helps bring incredible works of generative art to discerning collectors.

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. Passholders expand their access to unique collaborations with extraordinary artists, indispensable collector tools, curatorial experiences, artwork insights, fine art prints, a thriving community, and more.

Tender is committed to stewarding the growth of generative art and amplifying the voices of artists and collectors across the entire lifecycle: from creation to collection to curation, and back again. Every Pass minted and resold directly enables Tender to continue creating the platform and experiences that serve this mission.

——

TENDER Pass features unique artwork by punevyr. While all Passes are special, a small number of randomly generated, rarified tokens will come with boosted benefits. If you have a piece with a dark background of any kind, you likely possess one of the following:

Bonus Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Bonus trait get 1 guaranteed reserve spot on all TENDER x Collab projects

Grail Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Grail trait get 2 free mints on all TENDER x Collab projects


New Passholders may access our Discord server that’s linked from our website.
For TENDER Pass benefits and up-to-date details, please visit tender.art/pass


Artwork created with p5.js

---

TENDER x punevyr
July 2022
